50|$|In 1793, {{he joined}} the referendary of the Prussian war and council chamber. His overseer, Karl August von Hardenberg, quickly {{recognized}} his talent and encouraged him to join the diplomatic corps. In 1799, he went with Hardenberg to Berlin where he worked for as a Ministerialrat and later became a <b>senior</b> <b>financial</b> <b>officer</b> for the general directorate. As a result of Prussia's losses in the Fourth Coalition War of the Napoleonic Wars {{at the battle of}} Jena-Auerstedt, he went with Hardenberg in 1806 to Tilsit to work on the Prussian Reforms.|$|E
